    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-02T13:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-02T13:10:00-05:00" n="1453"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.24/8–2444: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-02T14:10:00-04:00"
                            >September 2, 1944—2:10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–659. Your airgram No. A–817, August 24, noon. The considerations outlined in
                    the Department’s telegram no. 864 of August 17, 6 p.m. do not apply with regard
                    to purchases made by Peru in other <pb facs="1559" n="1545" xml:id="pg_1545"/>
                    South American countries including Argentina, since there is no question of
                    violation of United States export controls.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
